  "name": "Rising Three Methods Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies the 'Rising Three Methods' candlestick continuation pattern on 4-hour timeframes. It initiates trades based on a strong bullish candle followed by three small-bodied bearish or neutral candles, culminating in a final bullish candle that confirms the pattern.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Design a TechnicalPattern trading algorithm (intermediate complexity, Python format) that detects and trades the \"Rising Three Methods\" candlestick continuation pattern on 4-hour timeframes. The pattern requires: (1) a strong bullish candle; (2) three consecutive small-bodied bearish or neutral candles with closes inside the first candle\u2019s real body; (3) a final bullish candle that closes above the first bullish candle\u2019s close. Use the Volume Weighted Moving Average (VWMA, period 20) as trend filter: only trade if the VWMA is sloping up over the last 10 bars. Enter long at the close of the confirmation (final) bullish candle, set stop-loss below the low of the entire pattern, and exit either at 2R profit or if price closes below the VWMA. Only one position at a time; skip signals if another pattern occurs before exit.",
